Stir gelatin and boiling water in medium bowl until completely dissolved. Pour into 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours. Dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin. Cut gelatin into 1-inch cubes. Place gelatin in large bowl. Add fruit and toss gently. Serve at once, or cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.